Integrating git with central services
=====================================

Many central git hosting services, such as GitHub and GitLab, provide an API to
perform actions such as creating repositories and filing pull requests.
git-spindle is a collection of git subcommands to make using these services
easier.

For example, to fork and clone a repository on GitHub, one can now simply use

    git hub clone seveas/whelk

With this git subcommand, you can perform various github actions, such as
creating or forking a repository from the command line.

To install the latest released version:

    pip install git-spindle

If you use windows, you'll want to install git and pip via msys2. Download
msys2 from http://msys2.github.io/ and use pacman to install pip and git:

    pacman -Syu
    pacman -S git
    pacman -S mingw-w64-i686-python2-pip

Usage:

(For detailed information, go to http://seveas.github.com/git-spindle)

Add an account to the configuration:
  git hub [options] add-account [--host=<host>] <alias>
Add a user as collaborator:
  git hub [options] add-collaborator <user>...
Add a deploy key:
  git hub [options] add-deploy-key [--read-only] <key>...
Add a repository hook:
  git hub [options] add-hook <name> [<setting>...]
Adds keys to your public keys:
  git hub [options] add-public-keys [<key>...]
Add user's fork as a named remote. The name defaults to the user's loginname:
  git hub [options] add-remote [--ssh|--http|--git] <user> [<name>]
Applies a pull request as a series of cherry-picks:
  git hub [options] apply-pr <pr-number>
Open the GitHub page for a repository in a browser:
  git hub [options] browse [--parent] [<repo>] [<section>]
Show a timeline of a user's activity:
  git hub [options] calendar [<user>]
Display the contents of a file on GitHub:
  git hub [options] cat <file>...
Clone a repository by name:
  git hub [options] clone [--ssh|--http|--git] [--parent] [git-clone-options] <repo> [<dir>]
List collaborators of a repository:
  git hub [options] collaborators [<repo>]
Configure git-spindle, similar to git-config:
  git hub [options] config [--unset] <key> [<value>]
Create a repository on github to push to:
  git hub [options] create [--private] [--description=<description>]
Lists all keys for a repo:
  git hub [options] deploy-keys [<repo>]
Edit a hook:
  git hub [options] edit-hook <name> [<setting>...]
Fork a repo and clone it:
  git hub [options] fork [--ssh|--http|--git] [<repo>]
List all forks of this repository:
  git hub [options] forks [<repo>]
Create a new gist from files or stdin:
  git hub [options] gist [--description=<description>] <file>...
Show all gists for a user:
  git hub [options] gists [<user>]
Show hooks that have been enabled:
  git hub [options] hooks
Show gitignore patterns for one or more languages:
  git hub [options] ignore [<language>...]
Show issue details or report an issue:
  git hub [options] issue [<repo>] [--parent] [<issue>...]
List issues in a repository:
  git hub [options] issues [<repo>] [--parent] [<filter>...]
Display github log for yourself or other users. Or for an organisation or a repo:
  git hub [options] log [--type=<type>] [<what>]
Display the contents of a directory on GitHub:
  git hub [options] ls [<dir>...]
Mirror a repository, or all repositories for a user:
  git hub [options] mirror [--ssh|--http|--git] [--goblet] [<repo>]
Create a graphviz graph of followers and forks:
  git hub [options] network [<level>]
Lists all keys for a user:
  git hub [options] public-keys [<user>]
Opens a pull request to merge your branch to an upstream branch:
  git hub [options] pull-request [--issue=<issue>] [--yes] [<yours:theirs>]
Remove a user as collaborator:
  git hub [options] remove-collaborator <user>...
Remove deploy key by id:
  git hub [options] remove-deploy-key <key>...
Remove a hook:
  git hub [options] remove-hook <name>
Render a markdown document:
  git hub [options] render [--save=<outfile>] <file>
List all repos of a user, by default yours:
  git hub [options] repos [--no-forks] [<user>]
Let the octocat speak to you:
  git hub [options] say [<msg>]
Set the remote 'origin' to github.:
  git hub [options] set-origin [--ssh|--http|--git]
Set up goblet config based on GitHub config:
  git hub [options] setup-goblet
Display current and historical GitHub service status:
  git hub [options] status
Display GitHub user info:
  git hub [options] whoami
Display GitHub user info:
  git hub [options] whois <user>...

Add an account to the configuration:
  git lab [options] add-account [--host=<host>] <alias>
Add a project member:
  git lab [options] add-member [--access-level=guest|reporter|developer|master|owner] <user>...
Adds keys to your public keys:
  git lab [options] add-public-keys [<key>...]
Add user's fork as a named remote. The name defaults to the user's loginname:
  git lab [options] add-remote [--ssh|--http] <user> [<name>]
Applies a merge request as a series of cherry-picks:
  git lab [options] apply-merge <merge-request-number>
Open the GitLab page for a repository in a browser:
  git lab [options] browse [--parent] [<repo>] [<section>]
Show a timeline of a user's activity:
  git lab [options] calendar [<user>]
Display the contents of a file on GitLab:
  git lab [options] cat <file>...
Clone a repository by name:
  git lab [options] clone [--ssh|--http] [--parent] [git-clone-options] <repo> [<dir>]
Configure git-spindle, similar to git-config:
  git lab [options] config [--unset] <key> [<value>]
Create a repository on gitlab to push to:
  git lab [options] create [--private|--internal] [--description=<description>]
Fork a repo and clone it:
  git lab [options] fork [--ssh|--http] [<repo>]
Show issue details or report an issue:
  git lab [options] issue [<repo>] [--parent] [<issue>...]
List issues in a repository:
  git lab [options] issues [<repo>] [--parent] [<filter>...]
Display GitLab log for a repository:
  git lab [options] log [<repo>]
Display the contents of a directory on GitLab:
  git lab [options] ls [<dir>...]
List repo memberships:
  git lab [options] members [<repo>]
Opens a merge request to merge your branch to an upstream branch:
  git lab [options] merge-request [--yes] [<yours:theirs>]
Mirror a repository, or all your repositories:
  git lab [options] mirror [--ssh|--http] [--goblet] [<repo>]
Protect a branch against force-pushes:
  git lab [options] protect <branch>
List protected branches:
  git lab [options] protected
Lists all keys for a user:
  git lab [options] public-keys [<user>]
Remove a user's membership:
  git lab [options] remove-member <user>...
List all your repos:
  git lab [options] repos [--no-forks]
Set the remote 'origin' to gitlab.:
  git lab [options] set-origin [--ssh|--http]
Remove force-push protection from a branch:
  git lab [options] unprotect <branch>
Display GitLab user info:
  git lab [options] whoami
Display GitLab user info:
  git lab [options] whois <user>...

Add an account to the configuration:
  git bb [options] add-account [--host=<host>] <alias>
Add a deploy key:
  git bb [options] add-deploy-key <key>...
Add privileges for a user to this repo:
  git bb [options] add-privilege [--admin|--read|--write] <user>...
Adds keys to your public keys:
  git bb [options] add-public-keys [<key>...]
Add user's fork as a named remote. The name defaults to the user's loginname:
  git bb [options] add-remote [--ssh|--http] <user> [<name>]
Applies a pull request as a series of cherry-picks:
  git bb [options] apply-pr <pr-number>
Open the GitHub page for a repository in a browser:
  git bb [options] browse [--parent] [<repo>] [<section>]
Display the contents of a file on BitBucket:
  git bb [options] cat <file>...
Clone a repository by name:
  git bb [options] clone [--ssh|--http] [--parent] [git-clone-options] <repo> [<dir>]
Configure git-spindle, similar to git-config:
  git bb [options] config [--unset] <key> [<value>]
Create a repository on bitbucket to push to:
  git bb [options] create [--private] [--description=<description>]
Lists all keys for a repo:
  git bb [options] deploy-keys [<repo>]
Fork a repo and clone it:
  git bb [options] fork [--ssh|--http] [<repo>]
List all forks of this repository:
  git bb [options] forks [<repo>]
Invite users to collaborate on this repository:
  git bb [options] invite [--read|--write|--admin] <email>...
Show issue details or report an issue:
  git bb [options] issue [<repo>] [--parent] [<issue>...]
List issues in a repository:
  git bb [options] issues [<repo>] [--parent] [<filter>...]
Display the contents of a directory on BitBucket:
  git bb [options] ls [<dir>...]
Mirror a repository, or all repositories for a user:
  git bb [options] mirror [--ssh|--http] [--goblet] [<repo>]
List repo privileges:
  git bb [options] privileges [<repo>]
Lists all keys for a user:
  git bb [options] public-keys [<user>]
Opens a pull request to merge your branch to an upstream branch:
  git bb [options] pull-request [--yes] [<yours:theirs>]
Remove deploy key by id:
  git bb [options] remove-deploy-key <key>...
Remove a user's membership:
  git bb [options] remove-privilege <user>...
List all repos of a user, by default yours:
  git bb [options] repos [--no-forks] [<user>]
Set the remote 'origin' to github.:
  git bb [options] set-origin [--ssh|--http]
Create a new gist from files or stdin:
  git bb [options] snippet [--description=<description>] <file>...
Show all gists for a user:
  git bb [options] snippets [<user>]
Display BitBucket user info:
  git bb [options] whoami
Display GitHub user info:
  git bb [options] whois <user>...

